subproject.corporate outcome: Capacities of national and local institutions enhanced to scale up proven MDG acceleration interventions and to plan, monitor, report and evaluate the MDG progress in the context of related national development priorities
subproject.description: Women, youth, persons with disabilities and other vulnerable groups have access to quality vocational training, business skills development and sustainable micro-finance services and assistance to the private sector, small and medium enterprises (SMEs) and tripartite mechanism. The programme will further promote and enhance the skills of young men, women as well as people living with disabilities, and HIV/AIS to build their capacity to ensure equal access to sustainable livelihood.
subproject.title: Youth Empowerment and Employme
